<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1756" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1756">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/173.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 4, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Panaman President signed, to-day, contract with Hebard and Company, to
                            construct railway in the province adjoining Costa Rica. Cost estimated
                            at million dollars and a half. Details of bond issue left for
                            consultation with State Department, Washington. It is contemplated
                            encumbering income from six million loan in New York City.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>